              {
                "dsDescriptionValue": {
                  "typeName": "dsDescriptionValue",
                  "typeClass": "primitive",
                  "multiple": false,
                  "value": "A tidy, documented, reproducible dataset of Colorado snowpack — snow water equivalent (SWE), snow depth, and water-year precipitation accumulation, in inches — at NRCS SNOTEL (automated, daily, since ~1980) and snow-course (manual, semimonthly, many back to the 1930s-40s) sites, liberated from the NRCS AWDB REST API into a single long-format CSV: one row per (source, site_id, datetime, variable). Each station carries its full period of record. Part of the Colorado Environmental Data Hub (CUPIDS Lab); implements issue #11. The headline product is basin SWE as a percent of normal (1991-2020 baseline). Note that the two networks (SNOTEL and snow course) are NEARBY but DISTINCT sites, not duplicate measurements of one point: they are complementary (snow courses extend the record before SNOTEL), and a co-located pair tracks closely but is not identical. precip_accum_in is water-year-cumulative (resets each Oct 1), not a daily increment; missing values are NA, never zero-filled. Each extract carries per-source provenance (source URL, retrieval time, SHA-256, license). Regenerated and re-audited monthly from the AWDB API; see the repository for the re-runnable pipeline."
                }
              }
            ]
